Attackers whose methods line up with the data-extortion group&nbsp;ShinyHunters&nbsp;have spent the past year walking into corporate Salesforce environments without exploiting a single flaw in the platform.

The way in has been the trust the organization had already extended, usually through the OAuth connections that tie Salesforce to the apps and third-party vendors around it.

